  "text": "It is a major source of cost in a supply chain and has a huge impact on responsiveness [CITATION_1] . is purchased solely due to seasonal changes in demand. c) Fill rate (order/case)-the fraction of order/demand that was met on time from inventory. It should not be averaged over time but over a specified number of units of demand (i.e. every thousand, million etc).This means that an inventory turnover leads to a decrease in average inventory levels and increase in annual sales [CITATION_2] . The highest inventory turnover ratio has a high level of liquidity; smaller risk of obsolescence and reduced investment in industry. On the other hand, low inventory level increases the risk of lost sales. Loss of sales results in money in the competitor's account, thereby improving cash flow, and it leads to a hedge factor i.e. to carry more items and more inventories than is necessary; further factor i.e.,",
